  "body": "# Problem\n\nThe keycard_signTypedData(signer, message) has been modelled after eth_signTypedData(signer, message). In eth_signTypedData the signer is the account used to sign the message. However in keycard_signTypedData a Keycard is used for this purpose so it unclear what the signer argument is used for. Ideally, we would remove it, changing the function to keycard_signTypedData(message)\n\nIf the signer argument is actually used for something it should be clearly documented so that dApps know what they have to pass and why.\n\n## Implementation\n\n The function should become keycard_signTypedData(message) and all references to signer should be removed.",
